{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1007,"text":"Now, Hegel -- he very famously said"},{"time":4016,"text":"that Africa was a place without history,"},{"time":6847,"text":"without past, without narrative."},{"time":8959,"text":"Yet, I'd argue that no other continent\nhas nurtured, has fought for,"},{"time":14811,"text":"has celebrated its history\nmore concertedly."},{"time":18303,"text":"The struggle to keep\nAfrican narrative alive"},{"time":21396,"text":"has been one of the most consistent"},{"time":23511,"text":"and hard-fought endeavors\nof African peoples,"},{"time":26444,"text":"and it continues to be so."},{"time":28441,"text":"The struggles endured and the sacrifices\nmade to hold onto narrative"},{"time":33176,"text":"in the face of enslavement, colonialism,\nracism, wars and so much else"},{"time":39249,"text":"has been the underpinning narrative"},{"time":41284,"text":"of our history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43434,"text":"And our narrative has not just\nsurvived the assaults"},{"time":46619,"text":"that history has thrown at it."},{"time":48438,"text":"We've left a body of material culture,"},{"time":52184,"text":"artistic magistery\nand intellectual output."},{"time":56101,"text":"We've mapped and we've charted\nand we've captured our histories"},{"time":60761,"text":"in ways that are the measure\nof anywhere else on earth."},{"time":65063,"text":"Long before the meaningful\narrival of Europeans --"},{"time":69643,"text":"indeed, whilst Europe was still\nmired in its Dark Age --"},{"time":73207,"text":"Africans were pioneering techniques\nin recording, in nurturing history,"},{"time":79287,"text":"forging revolutionary methods\nfor keeping their story alive."},{"time":84823,"text":"And living history, dynamic heritage --"},{"time":87809,"text":"it remains important to us."},{"time":90145,"text":"We see that manifest in so many ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94576,"text":"I'm reminded of how, just last year --\nyou might remember it --"},{"time":99448,"text":"the first members"},{"time":100643,"text":"of the al Qaeda-affiliated Ansar Dine"},{"time":103092,"text":"were indicted for war crimes\nand sent to the Hague."},{"time":106338,"text":"And one of the most notorious\nwas Ahmad al-Faqi,"},{"time":110920,"text":"who was a young Malian,"},{"time":112388,"text":"and he was charged, not with genocide,"},{"time":114538,"text":"not with ethnic cleansing,"},{"time":116478,"text":"but with being one\nof the instigators of a campaign"},{"time":120317,"text":"to destroy some of Mali's most\nimportant cultural heritage."},{"time":124762,"text":"This wasn't vandalism;"},{"time":126584,"text":"these weren't thoughtless acts."},{"time":129389,"text":"One of the things that al-Faqi said"},{"time":131242,"text":"when he was asked\nto identify himself in court"},{"time":134199,"text":"was that he was a graduate,\nthat he was a teacher."},{"time":137661,"text":"Over the course of 2012,\nthey engaged in a systematic campaign"},{"time":143318,"text":"to destroy Mali's cultural heritage."},{"time":147142,"text":"This was a deeply considered waging of war"},{"time":151491,"text":"in the most powerful way\nthat could be envisaged:"},{"time":154198,"text":"in destroying narrative,\nin destroying stories."},{"time":158210,"text":"The attempted destruction of nine shrines,"},{"time":161597,"text":"the central mosque"},{"time":163115,"text":"and perhaps as many as 4,000 manuscripts"},{"time":166632,"text":"was a considered act."},{"time":169729,"text":"They understood the power of narrative\nto hold communities together,"},{"time":175105,"text":"and they conversely understood\nthat in destroying stories,"},{"time":179347,"text":"they hoped they would destroy a people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182286,"text":"But just as Ansar Dine\nand their insurgency"},{"time":185807,"text":"were driven by powerful narratives,"},{"time":189047,"text":"so was the local population's defense\nof Timbuktu and its libraries."},{"time":193428,"text":"These were communities who've grown up\nwith stories of the Mali Empire;"},{"time":197682,"text":"lived in the shadow\nof Timbuktu's great libraries."},{"time":200867,"text":"They'd listened to songs\nof its origin from their childhood,"},{"time":204748,"text":"and they weren't about to give up on that"},{"time":207514,"text":"without a fight."},{"time":209120,"text":"Over difficult months of 2012,"},{"time":212356,"text":"during the Ansar Dine invasion,"},{"time":216332,"text":"Malians, ordinary people,\nrisked their lives"},{"time":220182,"text":"to secrete and smuggle\ndocuments to safety,"},{"time":224628,"text":"doing what they could\nto protect historic buildings"},{"time":227958,"text":"and defend their ancient libraries."},{"time":230282,"text":"And although they weren't\nalways successful,"},{"time":232960,"text":"many of the most important manuscripts\nwere thankfully saved,"},{"time":236667,"text":"and today each one of the shrines\nthat was damaged during that uprising"},{"time":241596,"text":"have been rebuilt,"},{"time":243412,"text":"including the 14th-century mosque\nthat is the symbolic heart of the city."},{"time":248654,"text":"It's been fully restored."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250494,"text":"But even in the bleakest periods\nof the occupation,"},{"time":254923,"text":"enough of the population of Timbuktu\nsimply would not bow"},{"time":260340,"text":"to men like al-Faqi."},{"time":262231,"text":"They wouldn't allow their history\nto be wiped away,"},{"time":265318,"text":"and anyone who has visited\nthat part of the world,"},{"time":268609,"text":"they will understand why,"},{"time":270461,"text":"why stories, why narrative, why histories\nare of such importance."},{"time":275618,"text":"History matters."},{"time":277978,"text":"History really matters."},{"time":281227,"text":"And for peoples of African descent,"},{"time":283487,"text":"who have seen their narrative\nsystematically assaulted over centuries,"},{"time":289129,"text":"this is critically important."},{"time":292131,"text":"This is part of a recurrent echo\nacross our history"},{"time":296203,"text":"of ordinary people making a stand\nfor their story, for their history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302385,"text":"Just as in the 19th century,"},{"time":304078,"text":"enslaved peoples of African\ndescent in the Caribbean"},{"time":308071,"text":"fought under threat of punishment,"},{"time":310409,"text":"fought to practice their religions,\nto celebrate Carnival,"},{"time":314584,"text":"to keep their history alive."},{"time":317343,"text":"Ordinary people were prepared\nto make great sacrifices,"},{"time":321247,"text":"some even the ultimate sacrifice,"},{"time":324497,"text":"for their history."},{"time":326965,"text":"And it was through control of narrative"},{"time":329434,"text":"that some of the most devastating\ncolonial campaigns were crystallized."},{"time":333794,"text":"It was through the dominance\nof one narrative over another"},{"time":337673,"text":"that the worst manifestations\nof colonialism became palpable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342795,"text":"When, in 1874, the British\nattacked the Ashanti,"},{"time":346712,"text":"they overran Kumasi\nand captured the Asantehene."},{"time":350364,"text":"They knew that controlling territory\nand subjugating the head of state --"},{"time":355161,"text":"it wasn't enough."},{"time":356742,"text":"They recognized that\nthe emotional authority of state"},{"time":360290,"text":"lay in its narrative"},{"time":363118,"text":"and the symbols that represented it,"},{"time":365704,"text":"like the Golden Stool."},{"time":367706,"text":"They understood that control of story\nwas absolutely critical"},{"time":373197,"text":"to truly controlling a people."},{"time":375468,"text":"And the Ashanti understood, too,"},{"time":377571,"text":"and they never were to relinquish\nthe precious Golden Stool,"},{"time":382005,"text":"never to completely\ncapitulate to the British."},{"time":387289,"text":"Narrative matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389657,"text":"In 1871, Karl Mauch, a German geologist\nworking in Southern Africa,"},{"time":395339,"text":"he stumbled across\nan extraordinary complex,"},{"time":399420,"text":"a complex of abandoned stone buildings."},{"time":402170,"text":"And he never quite recovered\nfrom what he saw:"},{"time":405510,"text":"a granite, drystone city,"},{"time":408767,"text":"stranded on an outcrop\nabove an empty savannah:"},{"time":412592,"text":"Great Zimbabwe."},{"time":415073,"text":"And Mauch had no idea who was responsible"},{"time":418589,"text":"for what was obviously\nan astonishing feat of architecture,"},{"time":423679,"text":"but he felt sure of one single thing:"},{"time":427246,"text":"this narrative needed to be claimed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431060,"text":"He later wrote that the wrought\narchitecture of Great Zimbabwe"},{"time":434928,"text":"was simply too sophisticated,"},{"time":437691,"text":"too special to have\nbeen built by Africans."},{"time":441248,"text":"Mauch, like dozens of Europeans\nthat followed in his footsteps,"},{"time":445799,"text":"speculated on who\nmight have built the city."},{"time":448603,"text":"And one went as far as to posit,"},{"time":451841,"text":"\"I do not think that I am far wrong\nif I suppose that that ruin on the hill"},{"time":457590,"text":"is a copy of King Solomon's Temple.\""},{"time":460165,"text":"And as I'm sure you know, Mauch,"},{"time":461920,"text":"he hadn't stumbled upon\nKing Solomon's Temple,"},{"time":464888,"text":"but upon a purely African\ncomplex of buildings"},{"time":468458,"text":"constructed by a purely\nAfrican civilization"},{"time":472109,"text":"from the 11th century onward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474089,"text":"But like Leo Frobenius,\na fellow German anthropologist"},{"time":478264,"text":"who speculated some years later,"},{"time":480633,"text":"upon seeing the Nigerian Ife Heads\nfor the very first time,"},{"time":484664,"text":"that they must have been artifacts\nfrom the long-lost kingdom of Atlantis."},{"time":490095,"text":"He felt, just like Hegel,"},{"time":492696,"text":"an almost instinctive need\nto rob Africa of its history."},{"time":499216,"text":"These ideas are so irrational,"},{"time":501646,"text":"so deeply held,"},{"time":503483,"text":"that even when faced\nwith the physical archaeology,"},{"time":506706,"text":"they couldn't think rationally."},{"time":508739,"text":"They could no longer see."},{"time":510761,"text":"And like so much of Africa's relationship\nwith Enlightenment Europe,"},{"time":514966,"text":"it involved appropriation, denigration\nand control of the continent."},{"time":520773,"text":"It involved an attempt\nto bend narrative to Europe's ends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525955,"text":"And if Mauch had really wanted\nto find an answer to his question,"},{"time":530172,"text":"\"Where did Great Zimbabwe\nor that great stone building come from?\""},{"time":534850,"text":"he would have needed to begin his quest"},{"time":537074,"text":"a thousand miles away from Great Zimbabwe,"},{"time":539787,"text":"at the eastern edge of the continent,\nwhere Africa meets the Indian Ocean."},{"time":543630,"text":"He would have needed to trace\nthe gold and the goods"},{"time":546862,"text":"from some of the great trading emporia\nof the Swahili coast to Great Zimbabwe,"},{"time":551701,"text":"to gain a sense of the scale and influence"},{"time":555184,"text":"of that mysterious culture,"},{"time":557088,"text":"to get a picture of Great Zimbabwe\nas a political, cultural entity"},{"time":562294,"text":"through the kingdoms and the civilizations"},{"time":565759,"text":"that were drawn under its control."},{"time":568242,"text":"For centuries, traders have been drawn\nto that bit of the coast"},{"time":574463,"text":"from as far away as India\nand China and the Middle East."},{"time":579233,"text":"And it might be tempting to interpret,"},{"time":581944,"text":"because it's exquisitely\nbeautiful, that building,"},{"time":585078,"text":"it might be tempting to interpret it"},{"time":588090,"text":"as just an exquisite, symbolic jewel,"},{"time":591642,"text":"a vast ceremonial sculpture in stone."},{"time":595022,"text":"But the site must have been a complex"},{"time":598203,"text":"at the center of a significant\nnexus of economies"},{"time":602782,"text":"that defined this region for a millennium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606395,"text":"This matters."},{"time":608135,"text":"These narratives matter."},{"time":610198,"text":"Even today, the fight to tell our story\nis not just against time."},{"time":615263,"text":"It's not just against\norganizations like Ansar Dine."},{"time":619010,"text":"It's also in establishing\na truly African voice"},{"time":623108,"text":"after centuries of imposed histories."},{"time":626775,"text":"We don't just have\nto recolonize our history,"},{"time":630230,"text":"but we have to find ways to build back\nthe intellectual underpinning"},{"time":635128,"text":"that Hegel denied was there at all."},{"time":637866,"text":"We have to rediscover African philosophy,"},{"time":640610,"text":"African perspectives, African history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645651,"text":"The flowering of Great Zimbabwe --\nit wasn't a freak moment."},{"time":649185,"text":"It was part of a burgeoning change\nacross the whole of the continent."},{"time":653182,"text":"Perhaps the great exemplification of that\nwas Sundiata Keita,"},{"time":657532,"text":"the founder of the Mali Empire,"},{"time":659749,"text":"probably the greatest empire\nthat West Africa has ever seen."},{"time":663713,"text":"Sundiata Keita was born about 1235,"},{"time":666835,"text":"growing up in a time of profound flux."},{"time":670928,"text":"He was seeing the transition\nbetween the Berber dynasties to the north,"},{"time":674800,"text":"he may have heard about the rise\nof the Ife to the south"},{"time":678094,"text":"and perhaps even the dominance\nof the Solomaic Dynasty"},{"time":683235,"text":"in Ethiopia to the east."},{"time":685516,"text":"And he must have been aware\nthat he was living through a moment"},{"time":689176,"text":"of quickening change,"},{"time":690895,"text":"of growing confidence in our continent."},{"time":694370,"text":"He must have been aware of new states"},{"time":697559,"text":"that were building their influence"},{"time":700047,"text":"from as far afield as Great Zimbabwe\nand the Swahili sultanates,"},{"time":705339,"text":"each engaged directly or indirectly\nbeyond the continent itself,"},{"time":711610,"text":"each driven also to invest in securing\ntheir intellectual and cultural legacy."},{"time":717794,"text":"He probably would have engaged\nin trade with these peer nations"},{"time":721246,"text":"as part of a massive continental nexus"},{"time":724773,"text":"of great medieval African economies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727608,"text":"And like all of those great empires,"},{"time":731231,"text":"Sundiata Keita invested in securing\nhis legacy through history"},{"time":736856,"text":"by using story --"},{"time":739744,"text":"not just formalizing\nthe idea of storytelling,"},{"time":745461,"text":"but in building a whole convention"},{"time":748162,"text":"of telling and retelling his story"},{"time":751547,"text":"as a key to founding a narrative"},{"time":753988,"text":"for his empire."},{"time":755607,"text":"And these stories, in musical form,"},{"time":758976,"text":"are still sung today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763371,"text":"Now, several decades\nafter the death of Sundiata,"},{"time":766699,"text":"a new king ascended the throne,"},{"time":769122,"text":"Mansa Musa, its most famous emperor."},{"time":773309,"text":"Now, Mansa Musa is famed\nfor his vast gold reserves"},{"time":776490,"text":"and for sending envoys to the courts\nof Europe and the Middle East."},{"time":781238,"text":"He was every bit as ambitious\nas his predecessors,"},{"time":785285,"text":"but saw a different kind of route\nof securing his place in history."},{"time":789576,"text":"In 1324, Mansa Musa\nwent on pilgrimage to Mecca,"},{"time":793607,"text":"and he traveled\nwith a retinue of thousands."},{"time":796962,"text":"It's been said that 100 camels\neach carried 100 pounds of gold."},{"time":803644,"text":"It's been recorded that he built\na fully functioning mosque"},{"time":807184,"text":"every Friday of his trip,"},{"time":809375,"text":"and performed so many acts of kindness,"},{"time":812520,"text":"that the great Berber chronicler,\nIbn Battuta, wrote,"},{"time":816383,"text":"\"He flooded Cairo with kindness,"},{"time":819366,"text":"spending so much in the markets\nof North Africa and the Middle East"},{"time":822927,"text":"that it affected the price of gold\ninto the next decade.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":828081,"text":"And on his return,"},{"time":829652,"text":"Mansa Musa memorialized his journey"},{"time":833885,"text":"by building a mosque\nat the heart of his empire."},{"time":839792,"text":"And the legacy of what he left behind,"},{"time":842462,"text":"Timbuktu,"},{"time":844163,"text":"it represents one of the great bodies\nof written historical material"},{"time":849447,"text":"produced by African scholars:"},{"time":851654,"text":"about 700,000 medieval documents,"},{"time":854900,"text":"ranging from scholarly works to letters,"},{"time":858123,"text":"which have been preserved\noften by private households."},{"time":861195,"text":"And at its peak,\nin the 15th and 16th centuries,"},{"time":864702,"text":"the university there was as influential"},{"time":868714,"text":"as any educational\nestablishment in Europe,"},{"time":871784,"text":"attracting about 25,000 students."},{"time":874802,"text":"This was in a city\nof around 100,000 people."},{"time":878392,"text":"It cemented Timbuktu\nas a world center of learning."},{"time":883594,"text":"But this was a very particular\nkind of learning"},{"time":887825,"text":"that was focused and driven by Islam."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891594,"text":"And since I first visited Timbuktu,"},{"time":893861,"text":"I've visited many other\nlibraries across Africa,"},{"time":896746,"text":"and despite Hegel's view\nthat Africa has no history,"},{"time":902065,"text":"not only is it a continent\nwith an embarrassment of history,"},{"time":906302,"text":"it has developed unrivaled systems\nfor collecting and promoting it."},{"time":911634,"text":"There are thousands of small archives,"},{"time":914479,"text":"textile drum stores,"},{"time":916401,"text":"that have become more than repositories\nof manuscripts and material culture."},{"time":921296,"text":"They have become fonts\nof communal narrative,"},{"time":924459,"text":"symbols of continuity,"},{"time":926743,"text":"and I'm pretty sure that many\nof those European philosophers"},{"time":929893,"text":"who questioned an African\nintellectual tradition"},{"time":933414,"text":"must have, beneath their prejudices,"},{"time":936315,"text":"been aware of the contribution\nof Africa's intellectuals"},{"time":941530,"text":"to Western learning."},{"time":942887,"text":"They must have known"},{"time":944149,"text":"of the great North African\nmedieval philosophers"},{"time":947001,"text":"who had driven the Mediterranean."},{"time":949517,"text":"They must have known about\nand been aware of"},{"time":952940,"text":"that tradition that is part\nof Christianity, of the three wise men."},{"time":957993,"text":"And in the medieval period,\nBalthazar, that third wise man,"},{"time":962006,"text":"was represented as an African king."},{"time":964733,"text":"And he became hugely popular"},{"time":967361,"text":"as the third intellectual leg\nof Old World learning,"},{"time":971370,"text":"alongside Europe and Asia, as a peer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975652,"text":"These things were well-known."},{"time":979552,"text":"These communities\ndid not grow up in isolation."},{"time":983200,"text":"Timbuktu's wealth and power developed\nbecause the city became"},{"time":987333,"text":"a hub of lucrative\nintercontinental trade routes."},{"time":991437,"text":"This was one center"},{"time":993627,"text":"in a borderless, transcontinental,"},{"time":996201,"text":"ambitious, outwardly focused,\nconfident continent."},{"time":1000874,"text":"Berber merchants,\nthey carried salt and textiles"},{"time":1004820,"text":"and new precious goods and learning\ndown into West Africa"},{"time":1008644,"text":"from across the desert."},{"time":1011224,"text":"But as you can see from this map"},{"time":1014719,"text":"that was produced a little time\nafter the life of Mansa Musa,"},{"time":1018988,"text":"there was also a nexus\nof sub-Saharan trade routes,"},{"time":1023614,"text":"along which African ideas and traditions"},{"time":1026898,"text":"added to the intellectual\nworth of Timbuktu"},{"time":1030545,"text":"and indeed across the desert to Europe."},{"time":1034420,"text":"Manuscripts and material culture,"},{"time":1038174,"text":"they have become fonts\nof communal narrative,"},{"time":1043125,"text":"symbols of continuity."},{"time":1045192,"text":"And I'm pretty sure that\nthose European intellectuals"},{"time":1049927,"text":"who cast aspersions on our history,"},{"time":1053685,"text":"they knew fundamentally\nabout our traditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1058155,"text":"And today, as strident forces\nlike Ansar Dine and Boko Haram"},{"time":1062889,"text":"grow popular in West Africa,"},{"time":1064826,"text":"it's that spirit of truly indigenous,\ndynamic, intellectual defiance"},{"time":1070460,"text":"that holds ancient\ntraditions in good stead."},{"time":1073438,"text":"When Mansa Musa made Timbuktu his capital,"},{"time":1076661,"text":"he looked upon the city\nas a Medici looked upon Florence:"},{"time":1080663,"text":"as the center of an open, intellectual,\nentrepreneurial empire"},{"time":1085746,"text":"that thrived on great ideas\nwherever they came from."},{"time":1089087,"text":"The city, the culture,"},{"time":1091360,"text":"the very intellectual DNA of this region"},{"time":1094502,"text":"remains so beautifully\ncomplex and diverse,"},{"time":1098219,"text":"that it will always remain, in part,"},{"time":1100912,"text":"located in storytelling traditions\nthat derive from indigenous,"},{"time":1105248,"text":"pre-Islamic traditions."},{"time":1107037,"text":"The highly successful form of Islam\nthat developed in Mali became popular"},{"time":1112668,"text":"because it accepted those freedoms"},{"time":1114741,"text":"and that inherent cultural diversity."},{"time":1117247,"text":"And the celebration of that complexity,"},{"time":1119698,"text":"that love of rigorously\ncontested discourse,"},{"time":1123747,"text":"that appreciation of narrative,"},{"time":1125615,"text":"was and remains, in spite of everything,"},{"time":1128913,"text":"the very heart of West Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1132347,"text":"And today, as the shrines and the mosque\nvandalized by Ansar Dine"},{"time":1136953,"text":"have been rebuilt,"},{"time":1138134,"text":"many of the instigators\nof their destruction have been jailed."},{"time":1141985,"text":"And we are left with powerful lessons,"},{"time":1144911,"text":"reminded once again\nof how our history and narrative"},{"time":1149291,"text":"have held communities\ntogether for millennia,"},{"time":1153222,"text":"how they remain vital\nin making sense of modern Africa."},{"time":1157906,"text":"And we're also reminded"},{"time":1159440,"text":"of how the roots of this confident,\nintellectual, entrepreneurial,"},{"time":1164488,"text":"outward-facing, culturally porous,\ntariff-free Africa"},{"time":1169296,"text":"was once the envy of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172181,"text":"But those roots, they remain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1174775,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1176012,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}